abstract: Haya Rashed al-Khalifa, a Bahraini lawyer who is the first woman in her country to serve as a diplomat, was elected president of the General Assembly. She is the first woman to be president of the 191-member body since 1969, when Angie Brooks of Liberia served, and she will take up her one-year position with the opening of the 61st General Assembly on Sept. 12. Ms. Khalifa, 53, who in the 1970's became one of the first women in Bahrain to practice law, has been Bahrain's ambassador to France and its permanent delegate to Unesco. She succeeds Jan Eliasson, Sweden's foreign minister.
